HTML/CSS NOTES

Notes:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8">
		<title> HTML Structure </title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1> This is a heading. </h1>
		<p><em>italic</em</p>
		<span></span>
		<button></button>
		<ul><li></ul>
		<a href=""></a>
		<img src="">
		<style></style
		<figure><img><figcaption></figure>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
	</body>
</html>

rich text = formatted while plain text = ascii
don't need to compile

Trees in html
	- child nodes
	- parent nodes
	- sibling nodes

CLASS/ID
<p id="" used once and only one>
<p class="" used multiple times and multiple ones"

comments <!-- This is a comment -->

CSS composed of ruleset:
element you're working on {
	text declarations: yuhhh
}

- comment /* */
- class selector = .book-summary
- id selectorr = #book-summary
- font-family Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;

CSS properties:
font-style = italic
text-decoration = underline
back-ground-color = rgb(red, green, blue)

CSS units: pixels and percentage
- absolute vs relative
